Java Access Modifiers

-It is used to provide "access" controls to classes, methods and variables in Java

-Types :
1. public
2. default
3. private
4. protected

Note - We are allowed to use only public and default access modifier for classes in Java

Public Access Modifier
- The classes, methods and variables that are assigned with "public" access specifier/modifier are accessible by all the other classes globally.

Default Access Modifier
- The classes, methods and variables that are assigned with "default or no" access specifier/modifier are accessible by classes belonging to same package.

Private Access Modifier
- The methods and variables that are declared as "private" are only visible within the same class.

Protected Access Modifier
- The methods and variables that are declared as "protected" are only visible by classes within the same package or its subclasses.
